text: Stadia was a cloud gaming service made by Google. Users were able to stream video games at up to 4K resolution at 60 frames per second. On September 29, 2022, Google said that they were shutting down Stadia. It was officially shut down on January 18, 2023. ==References== Category:2019 establishments in the United States Category:2023 disestablishments in the United States Category:Cloud computing Category:Google
